The problem is to prove that for any loop walk `p` from `u` to `v` on a simple graph `G`, the number of distinct vertices visited by `p` (i.e., the cardinality of the support set of `p`) is at most the number of distinct edges traversed by `p` plus one (i.e., the cardinality of the edge set of `p` plus one).

